description: Number of people killed in storm during the given year.

name: Subsistence incomes per person
description: The same as "Income per person (GDP/capita, inflation-adjusted $)" (version 9), but expressed in subsistence incomes per person ratehr than international $ per person. One subsistence income is equal to $1.25 per day (i.e. the lower poverty line), or $456.24 per year. Hence, we divided incomes epr person with 456.25.

name: Sugar per person (g per day)
description: The quantity of food consumption of sugar and sweeteners (grams per person and day). NOTE: data for 2004 are based on a rough extrapolation by Gapminder.

name: Suicide, age 0-14 (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality due to self-inflicted injury among children aged 0-14 years, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Suicide, age 15-29 (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality due to self-inflicted injury among persons aged 15-29 years, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Suicide, age 30-44 (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality due to self-inflicted injury among persons aged 30-44 years, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Suicide, age 45-59 (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality due to self-inflicted injury among persons aged 45-59 years, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Suicide, age 60+ (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality due to self-inflicted injury among persons aged 60+ years, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Suicide, men (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality due to self-inflicted injury among men, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted. This rate is calculated as if all countries had the same age composition of the population.

name: Suicides (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality due to self-inflicted injury, per 100 000 standard population, age adjusted. This rate is calculated as if all countries had the same age composition of the population.

name: Suicide, total deaths
description: Total number of estimated deaths from self-inflicted injury

name: Suicide women, (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality due to self-inflicted injury among women, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted. This rate is calculated as if all countries had the same age composition of the population.

name: Sulfur emissions per person (kg)
description: Sulfur emissions per person. Associated with acid rain. (Kilograms of sulfur per person and year).

name: Surface area (sq. km)
description: Surface area is a country's total area, including areas under inland bodies of water and some coastal waterways.

name: Surviving kids per woman
description: How many children a woman has on average that survives until their 35th birthday. It is based on the Total fertilirty rate and age-specific mortality.

name: Tax revenue (% of GDP)
description: Tax revenue refers to compulsory transfers to the central government for public purposes. Certain compulsory transfers such as fines, penalties, and most social security contributions are excluded. Refunds and corrections of erroneously collected tax revenue are treated as negative revenue.

name: TB programme (DOTS) coverage (%)
description: Percentage of total population that has been covered by DOTS programme, which is national TB programmes in finding and diagnosing people with TB.

name: TB deaths per 100 000, estimated, TB with HIV+
name_catalog: TB deaths /100k, est., TB with HIV+
description: Estimated number of deaths caused by TB (with HIV+) among 100,000 residents during the given year.

name: TB existing cases per 100 000, estimated, TB with HIV+
name_catalog: TB existing cases /100k, est., TB with HIV+
description: Estimated number of existing TB cases (with HIV+) among 100,000 residents during the given year.

name: TB new cases per 100 000, estimated, TB with HIV+
name_catalog: TB new cases /100k, est., TB with HIV+
description: Estimated number of new TB cases (with HIV+) among 100,000 residents during the given year.

name: TB deaths, estimated, TB with HIV+
name_catalog: TB deaths, estimated, TB with HIV+
description: Estimated number of deaths caused by TB (with HIV+) during the given year.

name: TB existing cases, estimated, TB with HIV+
name_catalog: TB existing cases, estimated, TB with HIV+
description: Estimated number of existing TB cases (with HIV+) during the given year.

name: TB new cases, estimated, TB with HIV+
name_catalog: TB new cases, estimated, TB with HIV+
description: Estimated number of new TB cases (with HIV+) during the given year.

name: Teen fertility rate (births per 1000 women ages 15-19)
description: The number of births per 1,000 women ages 15-19.

name: Tetanus deaths in newborn (per 1000 births)
description: Tetanus deaths in newborn (per 1,000 births)

name: Tetanus deaths in newborn (total deaths)
description: Tetanus deaths in newborn (total deaths)

name: Total GDP (PPP$, inflation-adjusted)
description: PPP GDP is gross domestic product converted to international dollars using purchasing power parity rates. A PPP dollar has the same purchasing power over GDP as the U.S. dollar has in the United States. Data are in constant 2005 international dollars.

name: Total GDP (US$, inflation-adjusted)
description: GDP at purchaser's prices is the sum of gross value added by all resident producers in the economy plus any product taxes and minus any subsidies not included in the value of the products. It is calculated without making deductions for depreciation of fabricated assets or for depletion and degradation of natural resources. Data are in constant 2010 U.S. dollars. Dollar figures for GDP are converted from domestic currencies using 2010 official exchange rates. For a few countries where the official exchange rate does not reflect the rate effectively applied to actual foreign exchange transactions, an alternative conversion factor is used.

name: Total GNI (PPP, current international $)
description: PPP GNI (formerly PPP GNP) is gross national income (GNI) converted to international dollars using purchasing power parity rates. An international dollar has the same purchasing power over GNI as a U.S. dollar has in the United States. Gross national income is the sum of value added by all resident producers plus any product taxes (less subsidies) not included in the valuation of output plus net receipts of primary income (compensation of employees and property income) from abroad. Data are in current international dollars. For most economies PPP figures are extrapolated from the 2011 International Comparison Program (ICP) benchmark estimates or imputed using a statistical model based on the 2011 ICP. For 47 high- and upper middle-income economies conversion factors are provided by Eurostat and the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD).

name: Total health spending per person (international $)
description: The average health expenditure per person, expressed in international dollars using PPP (Purchasing Power Parity).

name: Total health spending per person (US$)
description: The average health expenditure per person, expressed in US dollars using the average exchange rate.

name: Total health spending (% of GDP)
description: The sum of public and private health expenditure as a percentage of GDP.

name: Total number of dollar billionaires
description: Total number of billionaires in the country of their citizenship, provided by Forbes.com

name: Total population, with projections
description: Total number of population of both sexes, data after 2010 is based on the medium estimates from UN population division.

name: Total reserves (% of debt to foreigners)
description: International reserves to total external debt stocks.

name: Total sulfur emission (kilotonnes)
description: Total sulfur emissions per year. Associated with acid rain. 1000 tonnes of sulfur per year.

name: Total water withdrawal (billion cu meters)
description: Annual quantity of freshwater withdrawn for agricultural, industrial and municipal purposes, counted in billion cubic meters. It includes renewable freshwater resources as well as potential over-abstraction of renewable groundwater or withdrawal of fossil groundwater and eventual use of desalinated water or treated wastewater. It does not include other categories of water use, such as for cooling of power plants, mining, recreation, navigation, fisheries, etc., which are sectors that are characterized by a very low net consumption rate.

name: Trade balance (% of GDP)
description: External balance on goods and services (formerly resource balance) equals exports of goods and services minus imports of goods and services (previously nonfactor services).

name: Trade balance (US$, not inflation-adjusted)
description: External balance on goods and services (formerly resource balance) equals exports of goods and services minus imports of goods and services (previously nonfactor services). Data are in current U.S. dollars.

name: Traffic deaths men (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality among men due to traffic injury, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted. This rate is calculated as if all countries had the same age composition of the population.

name: Traffic deaths (per 100 000 people)
description: Traffic mortality per 100 000 standard population, age adjusted. This rate is calculated as if all countries had the same age composition of the population.

name: Traffic deaths women (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality among women due to traffic injury, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted, This rate is calculated as if all countries had the same age composition of the population.

name: Traffic mortality 15-29 (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality among persons aged 15-29 years due to traffic injury, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Traffic mortality 30-44 (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality among persons aged 30-44 years due to traffic injury, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Traffic mortality 45-59 (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality among persons aged 45-59 years due to traffic injury, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Traffic mortality 60+ (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality among persons aged 60+ years due to traffic injury, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Traffic mortality 0-14 (per 100 000 people)
description: Mortality among children aged 0-14 years due to traffic injury, per 100,000 standard population, age adjusted

name: Traffic deaths (total)
description: Total number of estimated deaths from road traffic accidents

name: Tsunami affected annual number
description: Total number of people getting affected, injured or killed in tsunami during the given year.

name: Tsunami deaths annual number
description: Number of people killed in tsunami during the given year.

name: Under-five mortality from CME (per 1000 born)
description: Death of children under five years of age per 1,000 live births. By The Inter-Agency Child Mortality Estimation Group (WHO, UNICEF, the United Nations Population Division, the World Bank, and independent experts) Sep 20 2011

name: Under-five mortality from IHME (per 1000 born)
description: Death of children under five years of age per 1,000 live births. Estimates and projections from the Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation, 1970-2015.

name: Underweight children
description: Percent of children under five who are more than two standard deviations below average weight for age.

name: Urban population
description: Urban population refers to people living in urban areas as defined by national statistical offices. It is calculated using World Bank population estimates and urban ratios from the United Nations World Urbanization Prospects. Aggregation of urban and rural population may not add up to total population because of different country coverages.

name: Urban population growth (annual %)
description: Urban population refers to people living in urban areas as defined by national statistical offices. It is calculated using World Bank population estimates and urban ratios from the United Nations World Urbanization Prospects.

name: Urban population (% of total)
description: Urban population refers to people living in urban areas as defined by national statistical offices. The data are collected and smoothed by United Nations Population Division.

name: Urban poverty (% urban people below national urban poverty line)
description: Urban poverty headcount ratio is the percentage of the urban population living below the national poverty lines.

name: Water and sanitation aid given (% of aid)
description: Percentage of total allocable aid for official development assistance (ODA) given by the donor countries that has been used in water and sanitation.

name: Water withdrawal (cu meters per person)
description: Total annual quantity of freshwater withdrawn per person per year, counted in cubic meters. It includes renewable freshwater resources as well as potential over-abstraction of renewable groundwater or withdrawal of fossil groundwater and eventual use of desalinated water or treated wastewater. It does not include other categories of water use, such as for cooling of power plants, mining, recreation, navigation, fisheries, etc., which are sectors that are characterized by a very low net consumption rate.

name: Wood removal (cubic meters)
description: The wood removed (volume of round wood over bark) for production of goods and services other than energy production (wood fuel), excluding felled trees left in the forest.

name: Working hours per week
description: Total amount of yearly working hours devided by 52 weeks.

name: CO2 emissions (1000 tonnes)
description: Total carbon dioxide emissions from the burning of fossil fuels during the given year (1000 metric tonnes of CO2).
